Rating: 4
I became obsessed with this recipe because I felt it had so much more potential than how it was written. I've made them every weekend for the past several weeks and have now perfected it. Here are my suggested amendments to increase the healthfulness, flavor, and heartiness: - use only whole wheat flour for the entire 1 1/3 cups of flour - mix 1/4 cup of finely chopped walnuts and 1 tsp ground cinammon into the dry ingredients - in a third bowl, mix 1 cup finely grated carrot (approx 1 large carrot), 1 cup raisins, 1 cups dried cranberries, and the zest of 1 medium sized orange. After your wet and dry ingredients are combined, fold these items in - once the batter is in the muffin tin, sprinkle some more of the chopped walnuts on top All of these additions require you to bake the muffins for a couple extra minutes - I find that 22-23 minutes works fine. I hope you enjoy!

