To BonnieLevy--the whole point of this recipe is that it is *not* the normal, dense, rich bran muffin. Rather, it bakes up light and fluffy, and does not overwhelm with its flavor, which makes it the perfect base for additions. The sour cream bran muffin recipe you praise so highly may be rich, but it is certainly not healthy with lots of butter and sour cream. If anyone wants a high fiber (especially if you use all ww pastry flour instead or ww and white), moist, light muffin that is very low in fat, this is the one!

