This recipe is a great, flexible base for many bran muffin variations, blueberry, apple, etc. I've found that using whole wheat pastry flour for all of the flour (ww and white) does not detract from the recipe, and I use 1.5 tsp baking powder + .5 tsp baking soda instead of the 2 tsp baking soda. This seems to give them a little more lift with the whole grain flour. For a no-cholesterol (and vegan) version, substitute soymilk soured with lemon juice for the buttermilk, and 1 tbsp flaxseeds, ground (measure before grinding) mixed with 1/4 cup water for the egg.

