I have made these several times and they have been great each time. I substitute one very ripe banana for the applesauce and leave all other ingredients the same. Moist and YUMMY! Even hubby can't believe they are low-fat!

Rating: 3
Just made them. Surprisingly moist for such a low fat muffin. Heed the advice not to overbake; mine were ready in less than 20 minutes. I doubled the recipe and made 18 larger muffins. I plan to freeze them. They will be great for packed lunches and snacks on the run. Admittedly, they are a little better with butter and jam :), but this is a nice basic recipe that you could add to.

Rating: 4
made these for a guest who needs low fat. i was shocked at how delicious they were. i used regular sugar. also added a little molasses to make it a tad more sweet. now they have become a staple. yum.

